The goldfish, on the other hand, needs to be fed 0.01 cups of fish food every day, but Cecilia has a lifetime supply of fish food, so she doesn't need to worry about running out. If one bag of dog food contains 110 cups, how many bags of dog food will Cecilia use in the first year of owning her puppy, disregarding the goldfish's food consumption? retuned None, delegating to next calculator. Explanation:\nIn the first year (365 days), Cecilia will feed the puppy 1 cup of dog food per day for the first 180 days and 2 cups per day for the remaining 185 days. This results in 180 cups + (2 cups/day * 185 days) = 180 + 370 = 550 cups of dog food. Since each bag contains 110 cups, Cecilia will need 550 / 110 = 5 bags. The result of 365 bags is incorrect.
